{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879941283,"sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab16760001eYwnzLCjPa0M4K","messageID":"msg_d7ab15138001xF5X5IL5tB0pwQ","sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5360a5aa1df9452c97ba1473","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-021: CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Implementation of build command for container image building\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-021.1: Build Command CLI Interface\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `build` Typer subcommand with options for workspace path, proxy configuration, cloud provider selection, output path, and verbose logging.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build command registration\n21: - **GIVEN** the Typer app is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** the CLI loads\n23: - **THEN** the `build` subcommand SHALL be registered as `agentcube build`\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Default workspace resolution\n26: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube build` without `-f` flag\n27: - **WHEN** the command executes\n28: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to current directory `\".\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Custom workspace path\n31: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-f /path/to/workspace`\n32: - **WHEN** the command executes\n33: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to the provided absolute or relative path\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Proxy configuration via flag\n36: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-p http://proxy:port` or `--proxy http://proxy:port`\n37: - **WHEN** the command executes\n38: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be passed to build options for dependency resolution\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Cloud provider selection\n41: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n42: - **WHEN** the command executes\n43: - **THEN** cloud provider SHALL override default build mode to `cloud`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Output path for build artifacts\n46: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--output /path/to/output`\n47: - **WHEN** the command completes\n48: - **THEN** build artifacts SHALL be copied or linked to the output path\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Command-level verbose logging\n51: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--verbose` on build command\n52: - **WHEN** the command executes\n53: - **THEN** logging level SHALL be DEBUG for build operation only\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### REQ-021.2: BuildRuntime Integration\n58: \n59: **Requirement:** The system SHALL instantiate `BuildRuntime` with verbose flag and invoke `build()` method with workspace path and options.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: BuildRuntime instantiation\n62: - **GIVEN** build command is invoked\n63: - **WHEN** command handler runs\n64: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)` SHALL be instantiated\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Pass options to BuildRuntime.build\n67: - **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n68: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` is called\n69: - **THEN** options dict SHALL include: `proxy`, `cloud_provider`, `output`, and any metadata overrides\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Handle BuildRuntime exceptions\n72: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` raises an exception\n73: - **WHEN** exception is caught\n74: - **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)` SHALL be invoked\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Display build success\n77: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n78: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` returns result dict\n79: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print success message with image name, tag, and build time using Rich formatting\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### REQ-021.3: Build Mode Resolution\n84: \n85: **Requirement:** The system SHALL determine build mode (local vs cloud) from metadata, with CLI `--cloud-provider` flag taking precedence.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Default to local build\n88: - **GIVEN** metadata has `build_mode: local` or no build_mode specified\n89: - **WHEN** `--cloud-provider` is not provided\n90: - **THEN** build mode SHALL be `local`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Cloud provider overrides to cloud mode\n93: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n94: - **WHEN** build mode is resolved\n95: - **THEN** build mode SHALL be `cloud` regardless of metadata\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Cloud mode requires cloud provider\n98: - **GIVEN** metadata has `build_mode: cloud`\n99: - **WHEN** no `--cloud-provider` is specified\n100: - **THEN** system SHALL raise error requiring cloud provider name\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### REQ-021.4: Local Docker Build Flow\n105: \n106: **Requirement:** The system SHALL execute local Docker build using `DockerService` when build mode is `local`.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Docker availability check\n109: - **GIVEN** build mode is `local`\n110: - **WHEN** build starts\n111: - **THEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` SHALL be called first\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Docker not available error\n114: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running\n115: - **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` fails\n116: - **THEN** `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` SHALL be raised\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Build image with DockerService\n119: - **GIVEN** Docker is available\n120: - **WHEN** local build proceeds\n121: - **THEN** `DockerService.build_image()` SHALL be called with:\n122:   - `dockerfile_path`: workspace/Dockerfile\n123:   - `context_path`: workspace\n124:   - `image_name`: `{agent_name}`\n125:   - `tag`: `{version}` or `latest`\n126:   - `build_args`: proxy settings if provided\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Image tagging convention\n129: - **GIVEN** metadata version is `1.2.3`\n130: - **WHEN** image is built\n131: - **THEN** image tag SHALL be `{agent_name}:1.2.3`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Fallback tag when no version\n134: - **GIVEN** metadata has no version\n135: - **WHEN** image is built\n136: - **THEN** image tag SHALL default to `{agent_name}:latest`\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### REQ-021.5: Version Increment Logic\n141: \n142: **Requirement:** The system SHALL increment version before local build and revert on failure.\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Patch version increment\n145: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.2.3`\n146: - **WHEN** build starts\n147: - **THEN** version SHALL become `1.2.4` before build\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Minor version increment\n150: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.2.0` and user requests minor bump\n151: - **WHEN** build starts\n152: - **THEN** version SHALL become `1.3.0`\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Major version increment\n155: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.0.0` and user requests major bump\n156: - **WHEN** build starts\n157: - **THEN** version SHALL become `2.0.0`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Pre-release version handling\n160: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.0.0-alpha.1`\n161: - **WHEN** build starts\n162: - **THEN** version SHALL increment pre-release to `1.0.0-alpha.2`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Version revert on build failure\n165: - **GIVEN** build fails after version increment\n166: - **WHEN** error is caught\n167: - **THEN** metadata version SHALL be reverted to original value\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Version string fallback\n170: - **GIVEN** version is not semver format (e.g., `v1.0`)\n171: - **WHEN** increment is attempted\n172: - **THEN** system SHALL append `.1` (e.g., `v1.0.1`) or use `{version}-1` fallback\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ### REQ-021.6: Cloud Build Flow\n177: \n178: **Requirement:** The system SHALL trigger cloud build when build mode is `cloud` and cloud provider is specified.\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Cloud build prerequisite validation\n181: - **GIVEN** build mode is `cloud`\n182: - **WHEN** build starts\n183: - **THEN** system SHALL validate cloud provider credentials/configuration\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Huawei cloud provider\n186: - **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider huawei`\n187: - **WHEN** cloud build is triggered\n188: - **THEN** system SHALL use Huawei Cloud Container Registry API\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Cloud provider not supported\n191: - **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider unknown-provider`\n192: - **WHEN** build starts\n193: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Unsupported cloud provider: unknown-provider\")`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Cloud build status polling\n196: - **GIVEN** cloud build is triggered\n197: - **WHEN** build is in progress\n198: - **THEN** system SHALL poll build status with progress indicator\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Cloud build timeout\n201: - **GIVEN** cloud build exceeds timeout (default 600s)\n202: - **WHEN** polling continues\n203: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `TimeoutError(\"Cloud build exceeded timeout\")`\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ### REQ-021.7: Build Validation Prerequisites\n208: \n209: **Requirement:** The system SHALL validate workspace prerequisites before build.\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Dockerfile existence check\n212: - **GIVEN** build is about to start\n213: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` runs\n214: - **THEN** system SHALL check for Dockerfile in workspace\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Missing Dockerfile\n217: - **GIVEN** no Dockerfile exists in workspace\n218: - **WHEN** validation runs\n219: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")`\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Metadata validation\n222: - **GIVEN** build is about to start\n223: - **WHEN** prerequisites are validated\n224: - **THEN** system SHALL verify `agent_metadata.yaml` exists and is valid\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Image name validation\n227: - **GIVEN** agent_name contains invalid characters\n228: - **WHEN** build starts\n229: - **THEN** system SHALL sanitize or reject invalid image names per Docker naming rules\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ### REQ-021.8: Build Output and Reporting\n234: \n235: **Requirement:** The system SHALL report build results with image details, build time, and next steps.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Build success output\n238: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n239: - **WHEN** result is returned\n240: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print:\n241:   ```\n242:   ✓ Build completed successfully\n243:   Image: {image_name}:{tag}\n244:   Image ID: {image_id}\n245:   Size: {image_size}\n246:   Build time: {build_time}s\n247:   ```\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Build result metadata update\n250: - **GIVEN** build succeeds\n251: - **WHEN** `_update_build_metadata()` runs\n252: - **THEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be updated with image info (name, tag, id, size)\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Verbose build logs\n255: - **GIVEN** `--verbose` is true\n256: - **WHEN** build runs\n257: - **THEN** Docker build logs SHALL be streamed to console\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Next step guidance\n260: - **GIVEN** build succeeds\n261: - **WHEN** output is printed\n262: - **THEN** CLI SHALL suggest next command: `agentcube publish` with appropriate flags\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n266: ### REQ-021.9: Proxy Configuration\n267: \n268: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support proxy configuration for dependency resolution during build.\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: Proxy via CLI flag\n271: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-p http://proxy:port`\n272: - **WHEN** build runs\n273: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be set as `build_arg` for Docker build\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Proxy environment variable fallback\n276: - **GIVEN** no `-p` flag but `HTTP_PROXY` env var is set\n277: - **WHEN** build runs\n278: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be read from environment\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Proxy for pip installs\n281: - **GIVEN** Python workspace with requirements.txt\n282: - **WHEN** build processes dependencies\n283: - **THEN** pip install SHALL use `--proxy` flag if proxy is configured\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Proxy for maven builds\n286: - **GIVEN** Java workspace with pom.xml\n287: - **WHEN** build processes dependencies\n288: - **THEN** maven settings.xml SHALL include proxy configuration\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## Data Types\n293: \n294: ```python\n295: # Build command options\n296: class BuildOptions(TypedDict, total=False):\n297:     workspace: str\n298:     proxy: Optional[str]\n299:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n300:     output: Optional[str]\n301:     verbose: bool\n302: \n303: # Build result structure\n304: class BuildResult(TypedDict):\n305:     image_name: str\n306:     image_tag: str\n307:     image_id: str\n308:     image_size: str\n309:     build_time: str\n310:     build_mode: str\n311:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n312: ```\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## CLI Flags Summary\n317: \n318: | Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n319: |------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n320: | `--workspace` | `-f` | str | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n321: | `--proxy` | `-p` | Optional[str] | None | Proxy URL for dependencies |\n322: | `--cloud-provider` | - | Optional[str] | None | Cloud provider name (huawei, etc.) |\n323: | `--output` | - | Optional[str] | None | Output path for artifacts |\n324: | `--verbose` | - | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Environment Variables\n329: \n330: | Variable | Description | Default |\n331: |----------|-------------|---------|\n332: | `HTTP_PROXY` | HTTP proxy for builds | - |\n333: | `HTTPS_PROXY` | HTTPS proxy for builds | - |\n334: | `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket | system default |\n335: \n336: ---\n337: \n338: ## Error Codes\n339: \n340: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n341: |-------|-----------|---------|\n342: | Docker unavailable | 1 | \"Docker is not available or not running\" |\n343: | Missing Dockerfile | 1 | \"Dockerfile not found in workspace\" |\n344: | Invalid cloud provider | 1 | \"Unsupported cloud provider: {name}\" |\n345: | Build failure | 1 | \"Build failed: {detail}\" |\n346: | Cloud build timeout | 1 | \"Cloud build exceeded timeout ({duration}s)\" |\n347: | Version increment failure | 1 | \"Failed to increment version: {detail}\" |\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ## Dependencies\n352: \n353: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n354: |---------|---------|---------|\n355: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n356: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation |\n357: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK |\n358: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Output formatting |\n359: | `semver` | >=3.0.0 | Version parsing |\n360: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | Metadata handling |\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ## Acceptance Checklist\n365: \n366: - [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — build command registered with Typer\n367: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` — BuildRuntime class implemented\n368: - [ ] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService for local builds\n369: - [ ] `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/` — Cloud provider implementations\n370: - [ ] Version increment logic with rollback on failure\n371: - [ ] Proxy configuration via flag and environment\n372: - [ ] Build prerequisites validation (Dockerfile, metadata)\n373: - [ ] Success/failure output with Rich formatting\n374: - [ ] Verbose mode streams build logs\n375: - [ ] Error handling with appropriate exit codes\n376: - [ ] Next step guidance after successful build\n377: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for build path\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Open Questions\n382: \n383: 1. Should build command support `--tag` override for custom image tags?\n384: 2. Should multi-platform builds (`--platform`) be supported in initial release?\n385: 3. Should build cache options (`--no-cache`, `--cache-from`) be exposed?\n\n(End of file - total 385 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-021: CLI build 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Implementation of build command for container image building\n\n**Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-021.1: Build Command CLI Interface\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `build` Typer subcommand with options for workspace path, proxy configuration, cloud provider selection, output path, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Build command registration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md","time":{"start":1775879941248,"end":1775879941280}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879941287,"sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab16250001xwRSStz43npBT4","messageID":"msg_d7ab15138001xF5X5IL5tB0pwQ","sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c7ea74559b9947fb910c18ec","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Type:** Implementation of publish command for agent deployment to Kubernetes (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment/Service)\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-022.1: Publish Command CLI Interface\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `publish` Typer subcommand with options for workspace, version, image repository credentials, deployment region, cloud provider, provider type (agentcube/k8s), node port, replicas, namespace, and verbose logging.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Publish command registration\n21: - **GIVEN** the Typer app is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** the CLI loads\n23: - **THEN** the `publish` subcommand SHALL be registered as `agentcube publish`\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Default workspace resolution\n26: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube publish` without `-f` flag\n27: - **WHEN** the command executes\n28: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to current directory `\".\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Version specification\n31: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--version 1.2.3`\n32: - **WHEN** the command executes\n33: - **THEN** version SHALL override metadata version for publishing\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Image repository URL\n36: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--image-url registry.example.com/myimage`\n37: - **WHEN** the command executes in local build mode\n38: - **THEN** image URL SHALL be used for image push target\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Image repository credentials\n41: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--image-username` and `--image-password`\n42: - **WHEN** the command executes\n43: - **THEN** credentials SHALL be used for Docker login to image repository\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Provider selection\n46: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--provider k8s`\n47: - **WHEN** the command executes\n48: - **THEN** deployment SHALL use standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Default AgentCube provider\n51: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--provider`\n52: - **WHEN** the command executes\n53: - **THEN** provider SHALL default to `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR)\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: NodePort specification\n56: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--node-port 30080` with `--provider k8s`\n57: - **WHEN** the command executes\n58: - **THEN** Kubernetes Service SHALL use specified NodePort (30000-32767)\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Replicas specification\n61: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--replicas 3` with `--provider k8s`\n62: - **WHEN** the command executes\n63: - **THEN** Deployment SHALL be created with 3 replicas\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Namespace specification\n66: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--namespace production`\n67: - **WHEN** the command executes\n68: - **THEN** deployment SHALL target the `production` namespace\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Command-level verbose logging\n71: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--verbose` on publish command\n72: - **WHEN** the command executes\n73: - **THEN** logging level SHALL be DEBUG for publish operation only\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### REQ-022.2: PublishRuntime Integration\n78: \n79: **Requirement:** The system SHALL instantiate `PublishRuntime` with verbose flag and provider, and invoke `publish()` method with workspace path and options.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: PublishRuntime instantiation\n82: - **GIVEN** publish command is invoked\n83: - **WHEN** command handler runs\n84: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)` SHALL be instantiated\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Pass options to PublishRuntime.publish\n87: - **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n88: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` is called\n89: - **THEN** options dict SHALL include: `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Handle PublishRuntime exceptions\n92: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` raises an exception\n93: - **WHEN** exception is caught\n94: - **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` SHALL be invoked\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Display publish success\n97: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n98: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` returns result dict\n99: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print success message with agent endpoint and status using Rich formatting\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### REQ-022.3: AgentCube Provider Prerequisites\n104: \n105: **Requirement:** The system SHALL validate that metadata contains required URLs for AgentCube provider deployment.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Router URL requirement\n108: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube`\n109: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url`\n110: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentCube provider requires router_url in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Workload manager URL requirement\n113: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube`\n114: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `workload_manager_url`\n115: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentCube provider requires workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Both URLs present\n118: - **GIVEN** metadata contains both `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n119: - **WHEN** AgentCube publish proceeds\n120: - **THEN** validation SHALL pass\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### REQ-022.4: Image Preparation Flow\n125: \n126: **Requirement:** The system SHALL prepare the container image for publishing via Docker push (local mode) or use explicit image URL.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Local image preparation with Docker push\n129: - **GIVEN** build mode is `local` and no `--image-url` provided\n130: - **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image()` runs\n131: - **THEN** system SHALL push image to registry using `DockerService.push_image()`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Image URL without credentials\n134: - **GIVEN** `--image-url` is provided but no credentials\n135: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n136: - **THEN** system SHALL assume image is already pushed and use provided URL\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Image URL with credentials\n139: - **GIVEN** `--image-url`, `--image-username`, and `--image-password` are provided\n140: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n141: - **THEN** system SHALL login, tag, and push image to specified URL\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Cloud image preparation\n144: - **GIVEN** build mode is `cloud`\n145: - **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image()` runs\n146: - **THEN** system SHALL use cloud provider's image registry URL\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Image tag from version\n149: - **GIVEN** metadata version is `1.2.3`\n150: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n151: - **THEN** image tag SHALL be `{agent_name}:1.2.3`\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### REQ-022.5: AgentCube CR Deployment\n156: \n157: **Requirement:** The system SHALL deploy AgentRuntime CR using `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` when provider is `agentcube`.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR creation\n160: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube` and prerequisites are met\n161: - **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n162: - **THEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` SHALL be called with agent spec\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Readiness probe configuration\n165: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port`\n166: - **WHEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n167: - **THEN** readiness probe SHALL be configured in CR spec\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Environment variable injection\n170: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `workload_manager_url` and `router_url`\n171: - **WHEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n172: - **THEN** env vars `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` SHALL be set in pod spec\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Session timeout configuration\n175: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n176: - **WHEN** CR spec is assembled\n177: - **THEN** `sessionTimeout` SHALL be set to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Image pull secret reference\n180: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n181: - **WHEN** CR spec is assembled\n182: - **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` SHALL reference `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR update\n185: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR already exists\n186: - **WHEN** publish is run again\n187: - **THEN** existing CR SHALL be patched/updated rather than recreated\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### REQ-022.6: Standard Kubernetes Deployment\n192: \n193: **Requirement:** The system SHALL deploy standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service using `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` when provider is `k8s`.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Kubernetes deployment creation\n196: - **GIVEN** provider is `k8s`\n197: - **WHEN** `_publish_k8s()` runs\n198: - **THEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` SHALL be called with deployment spec\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: NodePort allocation\n201: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--node-port 30080`\n202: - **WHEN** Service is created\n203: - **THEN** Service SHALL use specified NodePort\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Auto NodePort allocation\n206: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--node-port`\n207: - **WHEN** Service is created\n208: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL allocate ephemeral NodePort (30000-32767)\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Replica count\n211: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--replicas 3`\n212: - **WHEN** Deployment is created\n213: - **THEN** Deployment spec SHALL have `replicas: 3`\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Default replica count\n216: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--replicas`\n217: - **WHEN** Deployment is created\n218: - **THEN** Deployment SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness wait\n221: - **GIVEN** Deployment is created\n222: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n223: - **THEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` SHALL be called\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness timeout\n226: - **GIVEN** Deployment does not become ready within 120 seconds\n227: - **WHEN** wait completes\n228: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `TimeoutError(\"Deployment not ready after 120s\")`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Service URL reporting\n231: - **GIVEN** Service is created with NodePort 30080\n232: - **WHEN** publish completes\n233: - **THEN** result SHALL include `service_url: \"http://localhost:30080\"`\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### REQ-022.7: Namespace Management\n238: \n239: **Requirement:** The system SHALL ensure target namespace exists before deployment.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Namespace creation\n242: - **GIVEN** target namespace does not exist\n243: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n244: - **THEN** namespace SHALL be created via Kubernetes API\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n247: - **GIVEN** target namespace exists\n248: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n249: - **THEN** no-op SHALL occur\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Default namespace\n252: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--namespace`\n253: - **WHEN** deployment proceeds\n254: - **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ### REQ-022.8: Publish Metadata Update\n259: \n260: **Requirement:** The system SHALL update workspace metadata with deployment information after successful publish.\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Agent ID assignment\n263: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created successfully\n264: - **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata()` runs\n265: - **THEN** metadata `agent_id` SHALL be set to CR name\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Agent endpoint recording\n268: - **GIVEN** deployment completes with service URL\n269: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n270: - **THEN** metadata `agent_endpoint` SHALL be set to service URL\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Session ID generation\n273: - **GIVEN** publish completes\n274: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n275: - **THEN** metadata `session_id` SHALL be generated or preserved\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Deployment info recording\n278: - **GIVEN** k8s provider deployment completes\n279: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n280: - **THEN** metadata `k8s_deployment` SHALL include deployment name, service name, namespace, node_port\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Metadata persistence\n283: - **GIVEN** metadata updates are made\n284: - **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata()` completes\n285: - **THEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be written with `yaml.dump(exclude_none=True)`\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ### REQ-022.9: Publish Status Reporting\n290: \n291: **Requirement:** The system SHALL report publish results with deployment status, agent endpoint, and next steps.\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Publish success output\n294: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n295: - **WHEN** result is returned\n296: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print:\n297:   ```\n298:   ✓ Publish completed successfully\n299:   Agent: {agent_name}\n300:   Provider: {provider}\n301:   Endpoint: {agent_endpoint}\n302:   Status: {status}\n303:   ```\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider success\n306: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is deployed\n307: - **WHEN** publish completes\n308: - **THEN** output SHALL include CR name and namespace\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: K8s provider success\n311: - **GIVEN** Deployment + Service are deployed\n312: - **WHEN** publish completes\n313: - **THEN** output SHALL include service URL and node port\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Next step guidance\n316: - **GIVEN** publish succeeds\n317: - **WHEN** output is printed\n318: - **THEN** CLI SHALL suggest next command: `agentcube invoke` with appropriate flags\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ### REQ-022.10: Error Handling\n323: \n324: **Requirement:** The system SHALL handle publish failures with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisite failure\n327: - **GIVEN** metadata lacks router_url\n328: - **WHEN** publish validation runs\n329: - **THEN** system SHALL print error in red and exit with code 1\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Image push failure\n332: - **GIVEN** Docker push fails (auth error, network error)\n333: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n334: - **THEN** error SHALL be reported and exit code 1 returned\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API failure\n337: - **GIVEN** Kubernetes API is unreachable\n338: - **WHEN** deployment is attempted\n339: - **THEN** error SHALL be reported and exit code 1 returned\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness failure\n342: - **GIVEN** Deployment fails to become ready\n343: - **WHEN** wait timeout expires\n344: - **THEN** error SHALL include pod events and exit code 1\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: CRD not installed\n347: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube` but CRD not installed\n348: - **WHEN** CR creation is attempted\n349: - **THEN** error SHALL indicate CRD is missing and exit with code 1\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Data Types\n354: \n355: ```python\n356: # Publish command options\n357: class PublishOptions(TypedDict, total=False):\n358:     workspace: str\n359:     version: Optional[str]\n360:     image_url: Optional[str]\n361:     image_username: Optional[str]\n362:     image_password: Optional[str]\n363:     description: Optional[str]\n364:     region: Optional[str]\n365:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n366:     provider: str  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n367:     node_port: Optional[int]\n368:     replicas: Optional[int]\n369:     namespace: Optional[str]\n370:     verbose: bool\n371: \n372: # Publish result structure\n373: class PublishResult(TypedDict):\n374:     agent_name: str\n375:     provider: str\n376:     agent_id: Optional[str]\n377:     agent_endpoint: str\n378:     status: str\n379:     deployment_info: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n380:     publish_time: str\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## CLI Flags Summary\n386: \n387: | Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n388: |------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n389: | `--workspace` | `-f` | str | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n390: | `--version` | - | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version string |\n391: | `--image-url` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository URL |\n392: | `--image-username` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository username |\n393: | `--image-password` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository password |\n394: | `--description` | - | Optional[str] | None | Agent description |\n395: | `--region` | - | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n396: | `--cloud-provider` | - | Optional[str] | None | Cloud provider name |\n397: | `--provider` | - | str | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: agentcube or k8s |\n398: | `--node-port` | - | Optional[int] | None | NodePort for k8s Service |\n399: | `--replicas` | - | Optional[int] | None | Replicas for k8s Deployment |\n400: | `--namespace` | - | Optional[str] | None | Kubernetes namespace |\n401: | `--verbose` | - | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n402: \n403: ---\n404: \n405: ## Environment Variables\n406: \n407: | Variable | Description | Default |\n408: |----------|-------------|---------|\n409: | `KUBECONFIG` | Kubernetes config file | `~/.kube/config` |\n410: | `ROUTER_URL` | AgentCube router URL | - |\n411: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | AgentCube workload manager URL | - |\n412: | `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket | system default |\n413: \n414: ---\n415: \n416: ## Error Codes\n417: \n418: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n419: |-------|-----------|---------|\n420: | Missing router_url | 1 | \"AgentCube provider requires router_url in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n421: | Missing workload_manager_url | 1 | \"AgentCube provider requires workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n422: | Image push failure | 1 | \"Failed to push image: {detail}\" |\n423: | Kubernetes API failure | 1 | \"Kubernetes API error: {detail}\" |\n424: | Deployment timeout | 1 | \"Deployment not ready after {timeout}s\" |\n425: | CRD not installed | 1 | \"AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Run: kubectl apply -f ...\" |\n426: | Invalid node-port | 1 | \"NodePort must be between 30000-32767\" |\n427: | Namespace creation failure | 1 | \"Failed to create namespace: {detail}\" |\n428: \n429: ---\n430: \n431: ## Dependencies\n432: \n433: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n434: |---------|---------|---------|\n435: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n436: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation |\n437: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK |\n438: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Output formatting |\n439: | `kubernetes` | >=28.0.0 | Kubernetes client |\n440: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | Metadata handling |\n441: | `httpx` | >=0.24.0 | HTTP client |\n442: \n443: ---\n444: \n445: ## Acceptance Checklist\n446: \n447: - [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — publish command registered with Typer\n448: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` — PublishRuntime class implemented\n449: - [ ] `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` — AgentCubeProvider for CR deployment\n450: - [ ] `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` — KubernetesProvider for standard deployment\n451: - [ ] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService for image push\n452: - [ ] Image preparation flow (local push, cloud, explicit URL)\n453: - [ ] AgentCube CR deployment with readiness probe\n454: - [ ] K8s Deployment + NodePort Service deployment\n455: - [ ] Namespace management\n456: - [ ] Metadata update with deployment info\n457: - [ ] Success/failure output with Rich formatting\n458: - [ ] Verbose mode streams deployment logs\n459: - [ ] Error handling with appropriate exit codes\n460: - [ ] Next step guidance after successful publish\n461: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for publish path\n462: \n463: ---\n464: \n465: ## Open Questions\n466: \n467: 1. Should publish command support `--dry-run` for validation without deployment?\n468: 2. Should `--wait` flag be added to control readiness wait behavior?\n469: 3. Should publish support `--rollback` on deployment failure?\n470: 4. Should multi-region deployment be supported via `--region` flag?\n\n(End of file - total 470 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** Implementation of publish command for agent deployment to Kubernetes (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment/Service)\n\n**Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-022.1: Publish Command CLI Interface\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `publish` Typer subcommand with options for workspace, version, image repository credentials, deployment region, cloud provider, provider type (agentcube/k8s), node port, replicas, namespace, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish command registration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879941245,"end":1775879941284}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879941294,"sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab15d430019GXUiJsA8X4hoY","messageID":"msg_d7ab15138001xF5X5IL5tB0pwQ","sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_89201838ca254ec29c67ce14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `manifests`  \n6: **Language:** YAML  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Type:** Helm Chart implementation for AgentCube control plane components\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md, deployment/design.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-030.1: Chart.yaml Metadata\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Chart.yaml with apiVersion v1, name agentcube, version 0.1.0, and appVersion 1.0.0.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure\n21: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** Chart.yaml is created\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n24:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n25:   - `name: agentcube`\n26:   - `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n27:   - `version: 0.1.0`\n28:   - `appVersion: \"1.0.0\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Chart metadata keywords\n31: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n32: - **WHEN** metadata is defined\n33: - **THEN** keywords SHALL include: `agent`, `sandbox`, `kubernetes`, `volcano`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Chart maintainers\n36: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n37: - **WHEN** maintainers are defined\n38: - **THEN** maintainers SHALL include Volcano Authors with email `volcano-sh@googlegroups.com`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Chart home and sources\n41: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n42: - **WHEN** home and sources are defined\n43: - **THEN** they SHALL reference `https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### REQ-030.2: values.yaml Configuration Tree\n48: \n49: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement values.yaml with complete configuration tree for Redis, Router, WorkloadManager, and Volcano Scheduler.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Redis configuration\n52: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n53: - **WHEN** redis configuration is defined\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n55:   - `redis.addr: \"\"` (empty default, user must provide)\n56:   - `redis.password: \"\"` (empty default for non-auth Redis)\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Router replicas and image\n59: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n60: - **WHEN** router configuration is defined\n61: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n62:   - `router.replicas: 1`\n63:   - `router.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router`\n64:   - `router.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n65:   - `router.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Router service configuration\n68: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n69: - **WHEN** router service is defined\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n71:   - `router.service.type: ClusterIP`\n72:   - `router.service.port: 8080`\n73:   - `router.service.targetPort: 8080`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Router resources\n76: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n77: - **WHEN** router resources are defined\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n79:   - `router.resources.limits.cpu: 500m`\n80:   - `router.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi`\n81:   - `router.resources.requests.cpu: 100m`\n82:   - `router.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi`\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Router RBAC toggle\n85: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n86: - **WHEN** router.rbac configuration is defined\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n88:   - `router.rbac.create: false` (disabled by default)\n89:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` (empty for auto-generated or default)\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager replicas and image\n92: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n93: - **WHEN** workloadmanager configuration is defined\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n95:   - `workloadmanager.replicas: 1`\n96:   - `workloadmanager.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager`\n97:   - `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n98:   - `workloadmanager.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager service configuration\n101: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n102: - **WHEN** workloadmanager service is defined\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n104:   - `workloadmanager.service.type: ClusterIP`\n105:   - `workloadmanager.service.port: 8080`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager resources\n108: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n109: - **WHEN** workloadmanager resources are defined\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n111:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 500m`\n112:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi`\n113:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu: 100m`\n114:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi`\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager extraEnv\n117: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n118: - **WHEN** workloadmanager.extraEnv is defined\n119: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` for additional environment variables\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler enabled toggle\n122: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n123: - **WHEN** volcano.scheduler configuration is defined\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n125:   - `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (disabled by default)\n126:   - `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 1`\n127:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler`\n128:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n129:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Image pull secrets\n132: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n133: - **WHEN** imagePullSecrets is defined\n134: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` by default\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Name overrides\n137: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n138: - **WHEN** nameOverride and fullnameOverride are defined\n139: - **THEN** they SHALL be empty strings `\"\"` by default\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Router extraEnv\n142: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n143: - **WHEN** router.extraEnv is defined\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` for additional environment variables\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Router config\n147: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n148: - **WHEN** router.config is defined\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty object `{}` for additional container configuration\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### REQ-030.3: Workload Manager Deployment Template\n154: \n155: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Workload Manager Deployment template with correct environment variables, probes, and resource configuration.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Deployment metadata\n158: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n159: - **WHEN** Workload Manager Deployment is created\n160: - **THEN** metadata SHALL include:\n161:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n162:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n163:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Workload Manager replicas from values\n166: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.replicas: 2`\n167: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n168: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `2`\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image from values\n171: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has custom image repository\n172: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n173: - **THEN** container image SHALL be `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Workload Manager environment variables\n176: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n177: - **WHEN** container env is defined\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n179:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from fieldRef `metadata.namespace`\n180:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}`\n181:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from Secret `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password`\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Workload Manager extraEnv injection\n184: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.extraEnv` entries\n185: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n186: - **THEN** extraEnv entries SHALL be injected into container env\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Workload Manager args\n189: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n190: - **WHEN** container args are defined\n191: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n192:   - `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n193:   - `--runtime-class-name=` (empty)\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Workload Manager liveness probe\n196: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n197: - **WHEN** livenessProbe is defined\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n199:   - `httpGet.path: /health`\n200:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n201:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 10`\n202:   - `periodSeconds: 10`\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Workload Manager readiness probe\n205: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n206: - **WHEN** readinessProbe is defined\n207: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n208:   - `httpGet.path: /health`\n209:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n210:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 5`\n211:   - `periodSeconds: 5`\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Workload Manager resources from values\n214: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.resources` defined\n215: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n216: - **THEN** `resources` SHALL be rendered from values using `toYaml`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image pull secrets\n219: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `imagePullSecrets` entries\n220: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n221: - **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` SHALL be injected into pod spec\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Workload Manager service account\n224: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n225: - **WHEN** serviceAccountName is defined\n226: - **THEN** it SHALL be `workloadmanager`\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Service\n229: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n230: - **WHEN** Workload Manager Service is created\n231: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n232:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n233:   - `type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}`\n234:   - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n235:   - `targetPort: http`\n236:   - Selector: `app: workloadmanager`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ### REQ-030.4: Router Deployment Template\n241: \n242: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Router Deployment template with correct environment variables, probes, and WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL.\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: Router Deployment metadata\n245: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n246: - **WHEN** Router Deployment is created\n247: - **THEN** metadata SHALL include:\n248:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n249:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n250:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Router replicas from values\n253: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.replicas: 3`\n254: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n255: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `3`\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Router image from values\n258: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has custom router image\n259: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n260: - **THEN** container image SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}`\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Router environment variables\n263: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n264: - **WHEN** container env is defined\n265: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n266:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from fieldRef `metadata.namespace`\n267:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}`\n268:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from Secret `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password`\n269:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"`\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Router extraEnv injection\n272: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.extraEnv` entries\n273: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n274: - **THEN** extraEnv entries SHALL be injected into container env\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Router args\n277: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n278: - **WHEN** container args are defined\n279: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n280:   - `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n281:   - `--debug`\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: Router liveness probe\n284: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n285: - **WHEN** livenessProbe is defined\n286: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n287:   - `httpGet.path: /health/live`\n288:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n289:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 1`\n290:   - `periodSeconds: 2`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Router readiness probe\n293: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n294: - **WHEN** readinessProbe is defined\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n296:   - `httpGet.path: /health/ready`\n297:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n298:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 1`\n299:   - `periodSeconds: 2`\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Router service account conditional\n302: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.serviceAccountName: \"custom-sa\"`\n303: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n304: - **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL be `custom-sa`\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: Router service account empty\n307: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"`\n308: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n309: - **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL NOT be set (use default)\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Router Service\n312: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n313: - **WHEN** Router Service is created\n314: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n315:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n316:   - `type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}`\n317:   - `port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}`\n318:   - `targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n319:   - Selector: `app: agentcube-router`\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ### REQ-030.5: Workload Manager RBAC\n324: \n325: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Workload Manager RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) with correct permissions.\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ServiceAccount\n328: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n329: - **WHEN** Workload Manager ServiceAccount is created\n330: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n331:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n332:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n333:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole sandbox permissions\n336: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n337: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n338: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n339:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`, `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole extension resources\n342: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n343: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n344: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n345:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n346:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n347:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole warm pool status\n350: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n351: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n352: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n353:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n354:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n355:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n358: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n359: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n360: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n361:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n362:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n363:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n364:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n365:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`, `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n368: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n369: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n370: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n371:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n372:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n373:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n374:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n375:   - `verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]`\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole pod permissions\n378: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n379: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n380: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n381:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n382:   - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n383:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole token review\n386: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n387: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n388: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n389:   - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n390:   - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n391:   - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole secret permissions\n394: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n395: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n396: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n397:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n398:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n399:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding\n402: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n403: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is created\n404: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n405:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n406:   - Subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: workloadmanager`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n407:   - RoleRef: `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: workloadmanager`, `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ### REQ-030.6: Router RBAC (Optional)\n412: \n413: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement optional Router RBAC resources controlled by `router.rbac.create` flag.\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: Router RBAC disabled by default\n416: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.rbac.create: false`\n417: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n418: - **THEN** Router RBAC resources SHALL NOT be created\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled\n421: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.rbac.create: true`\n422: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n423: - **THEN** Router ServiceAccount, Role, and RoleBinding SHALL be created\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount name\n426: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n427: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n428: - **THEN** name SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: Router Role secret permissions\n431: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n432: - **WHEN** Role rules are defined\n433: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n434:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n435:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n436:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding\n439: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n440: - **WHEN** RoleBinding is created\n441: - **THEN** it SHALL reference:\n442:   - Subject: ServiceAccount with default name\n443:   - RoleRef: Role with same name\n444: \n445: ---\n446: \n447: ### REQ-030.7: Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n448: \n449: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement optional Volcano Agent Scheduler resources controlled by `volcano.scheduler.enabled` flag.\n450: \n451: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler disabled by default\n452: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false`\n453: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n454: - **THEN** Volcano Scheduler resources SHALL NOT be created\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler enabled\n457: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n458: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n459: - **THEN** ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, and Deployment SHALL be created\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n462: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n463: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n464: - **THEN** name SHALL be `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n465: \n466: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ConfigMap\n467: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n468: - **WHEN** ConfigMap is created\n469: - **THEN** it SHALL include `agent-scheduler.conf` with:\n470:   - `actions: \"allocate\"`\n471:   - `tiers:` with `plugins: \"predicates,nodeorder\"`\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole CRD permissions\n474: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n475: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n476: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n477:   - `apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]`\n478:   - `resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]`\n479:   - `verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]`\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole pod permissions\n482: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n483: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n484: - **THEN** it SHALL include comprehensive pod permissions:\n485:   - `pods`, `pods/status`, `pods/binding`, `pods/disruptionbudgets`\n486:   - `persistentvolumeclaims`, `persistentvolumes`\n487:   - `nodes`, `namespaces`, `services`, `replicationcontrollers`\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole scheduling permissions\n490: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n491: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n492: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n493:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.k8s.io\"]`\n494:   - `resources: [\"priorityclasses\"]`\n495:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n496:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.incubator.k8s.io\", \"scheduling.volcano.sh\"]`\n497:   - `resources: [\"podgroups\"]`\n498:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\", \"update\"]`\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole storage permissions\n501: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n502: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n503: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n504:   - `apiGroups: [\"storage.k8s.io\"]`\n505:   - `resources: [\"storageclasses\", \"csinodes\", \"csidrivers\", \"csistoragecapacities\", \"volumeattachments\"]`\n506:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\"]`\n507: \n508: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole configmap permissions\n509: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n510: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n511: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n512:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n513:   - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n514:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"update\"]`\n515: \n516: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n517: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n518: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is created\n519: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n520:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler-role`\n521:   - Subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n522:   - RoleRef: `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Service\n525: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n526: - **WHEN** Service is created\n527: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n528:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler-service`\n529:   - `port: 8080`, `targetPort: 8080`, `name: metrics`\n530:   - Annotations: `prometheus.io/scrape: \"true\"`, `prometheus.io/port: \"8080\"`\n531:   - Selector: `app: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n532: \n533: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Deployment args\n534: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n535: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n536: - **THEN** container args SHALL include:\n537:   - `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`\n538:   - `--config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf`\n539: \n540: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Deployment volumes\n541: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n542: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n543: - **THEN** it SHALL include volumes:\n544:   - `name: config`, `configMap.name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap`\n545:   - `name: empty`, `emptyDir: {}`\n546: \n547: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler security context\n548: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n549: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n550: - **THEN** container securityContext SHALL include:\n551:   - `runAsNonRoot: true`\n552:   - `runAsUser: 1000`\n553: \n554: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler replicas from values\n555: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 2`\n556: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n557: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `2`\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ### REQ-030.8: Redis Secret Template\n562: \n563: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Redis Secret template to store Redis password.\n564: \n565: #### Scenario: Redis Secret creation\n566: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n567: - **WHEN** Redis Secret is created\n568: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n569:   - `name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis`\n570:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n571:   - `type: Opaque`\n572: \n573: #### Scenario: Redis Secret data\n574: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `redis.password: \"mysecret\"`\n575: - **WHEN** Secret is rendered\n576: - **THEN** `stringData.password` SHALL be `\"mysecret\"`\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Redis Secret labels\n579: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n580: - **WHEN** Secret labels are defined\n581: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n582:   - `app.kubernetes.io/name: redis`\n583:   - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n584: \n585: ---\n586: \n587: ### REQ-030.9: CRD Files\n588: \n589: **Requirement:** The system SHALL include CRD files for agentruntimes and codeinterpreters.\n590: \n591: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD existence\n592: - **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n593: - **WHEN** CRDs are applied\n594: - **THEN** `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` SHALL be created\n595: \n596: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD group and version\n597: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CRD is applied\n598: - **WHEN** CRD spec is validated\n599: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n600:   - `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n601:   - `spec.versions[0].name: v1alpha1`\n602: \n603: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD existence\n604: - **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n605: - **WHEN** CRDs are applied\n606: - **THEN** `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` SHALL be created\n607: \n608: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD group and version\n609: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreter CRD is applied\n610: - **WHEN** CRD spec is validated\n611: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n612:   - `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n613:   - `spec.versions[0].name: v1alpha1`\n614: \n615: #### Scenario: CRD installation order\n616: - **GIVEN** helm install is run\n617: - **WHEN** chart is installed\n618: - **THEN** CRDs SHALL be installed before other resources\n619: \n620: ---\n621: \n622: ### REQ-030.10: .helmignore\n623: \n624: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement .helmignore file to exclude unnecessary files from chart packaging.\n625: \n626: #### Scenario: Git files ignored\n627: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n628: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n629: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.git/`, `.gitignore`\n630: \n631: #### Scenario: Version control files ignored\n632: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n633: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n634: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.bzr/`, `.bzrignore`, `.hg/`, `.hgignore`, `.svn/`\n635: \n636: #### Scenario: Temporary files ignored\n637: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n638: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n639: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `*.swp`, `*.bak`, `*.tmp`, `*.orig`, `*~`\n640: \n641: #### Scenario: IDE files ignored\n642: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n643: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n644: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.project`, `.idea/`, `*.tmproj`, `.vscode/`\n645: \n646: #### Scenario: Test files ignored\n647: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n648: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n649: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `tests/`\n650: \n651: #### Scenario: Documentation files ignored\n652: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n653: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n654: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `*.md` but NOT `!README.md`\n655: \n656: ---\n657: \n658: ### REQ-030.11: Helm Lint and Template Validation\n659: \n660: **Requirement:** The system SHALL pass `helm lint` without errors and `helm template` shall generate valid YAML.\n661: \n662: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n663: - **GIVEN** chart structure is complete\n664: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is run\n665: - **THEN** it SHALL return no errors\n666: \n667: #### Scenario: Helm template generates valid YAML\n668: - **GIVEN** chart structure is complete\n669: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n670: - **THEN** output SHALL be valid YAML that can be parsed\n671: \n672: #### Scenario: Helm template with custom values\n673: - **GIVEN** custom values file is provided\n674: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base -f custom-values.yaml` is run\n675: - **THEN** output SHALL reflect custom values overrides\n676: \n677: #### Scenario: Helm template with Volcano enabled\n678: - **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` is passed\n679: - **WHEN** `helm template` is run\n680: - **THEN** output SHALL include Volcano Scheduler resources\n681: \n682: #### Scenario: Helm template with Router RBAC enabled\n683: - **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true` is passed\n684: - **WHEN** `helm template` is run\n685: - **THEN** output SHALL include Router RBAC resources\n686: \n687: ---\n688: \n689: ### REQ-030.12: Multi-Environment Support\n690: \n691: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support multi-environment deployment through values overrides.\n692: \n693: #### Scenario: Development environment values\n694: - **GIVEN** development values file is provided\n695: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `-f values-dev.yaml`\n696: - **THEN** all components SHALL use development-appropriate settings (e.g., lower resources)\n697: \n698: #### Scenario: Production environment values\n699: - **GIVEN** production values file is provided\n700: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `-f values-prod.yaml`\n701: - **THEN** all components SHALL use production-appropriate settings (e.g., higher replicas, resources)\n702: \n703: #### Scenario: Region-specific Redis configuration\n704: - **GIVEN** different regions have different Redis addresses\n705: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `--set redis.addr=redis-region1.svc:6379`\n706: - **THEN** components SHALL connect to specified Redis address\n707: \n708: #### Scenario: Custom image repository override\n709: - **GIVEN** organization uses private registry\n710: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `--set router.image.repository=myregistry.com/router`\n711: - **THEN** Router SHALL use custom image repository\n712: \n713: ---\n714: \n715: ## Data Types\n716: \n717: ```yaml\n718: # values.yaml structure\n719: values:\n720:   imagePullSecrets: []\n721:   nameOverride: \"\"\n722:   fullnameOverride: \"\"\n723:   \n724:   redis:\n725:     addr: string       # Required: Redis address\n726:     password: string   # Optional: Redis password\n727:   \n728:   router:\n729:     replicas: int\n730:     image:\n731:       repository: string\n732:       pullPolicy: string\n733:       tag: string\n734:     service:\n735:       type: string\n736:       port: int\n737:       targetPort: int\n738:     resources:\n739:       limits:\n740:         cpu: string\n741:         memory: string\n742:       requests:\n743:         cpu: string\n744:         memory: string\n745:     config: object\n746:     extraEnv: []\n747:     serviceAccountName: string\n748:     rbac:\n749:       create: bool\n750:   \n751:   workloadmanager:\n752:     replicas: int\n753:     image:\n754:       repository: string\n755:       pullPolicy: string\n756:       tag: string\n757:     service:\n758:       type: string\n759:       port: int\n760:     resources:\n761:       limits:\n762:         cpu: string\n763:         memory: string\n764:       requests:\n765:         cpu: string\n766:         memory: string\n767:     extraEnv: []\n768:   \n769:   volcano:\n770:     scheduler:\n771:       enabled: bool\n772:       replicas: int\n773:       image:\n774:         repository: string\n775:         pullPolicy: string\n776:         tag: string\n777: ```\n778: \n779: ---\n780: \n781: ## File Structure\n782: \n783: ```\n784: manifests/charts/base/\n785: ├── Chart.yaml\n786: ├── values.yaml\n787: ├── .helmignore\n788: ├── crds/\n789: │   ├── agentruntime.yaml\n790: │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml\n791: └── templates/\n792:     ├── _helpers.tpl\n793:     ├── redis-secret.yaml\n794:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n795:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n796:     ├── rbac/\n797:     │   └── workloadmanager.yaml\n798:     ├── rbac-router.yaml\n799:     └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml\n800: ```\n801: \n802: ---\n803: \n804: ## Environment Variables\n805: \n806: | Variable | Component | Description | Source |\n807: |----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n808: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Namespace from downward API | fieldRef |\n809: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis address | values.redis.addr |\n810: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis password | Secret |\n811: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager URL | Constructed from values |\n812: \n813: ---\n814: \n815: ## Error Codes\n816: \n817: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n818: |-------|-----------|---------|\n819: | Chart validation failure | 1 | `helm lint` failed: {detail} |\n820: | Template render failure | 1 | `helm template` failed: {detail} |\n821: | CRD installation failure | 1 | Failed to install CRD: {detail} |\n822: | Redis address not provided | 1 | `redis.addr` is required in values |\n823: | Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | YAML parse error in {file}: {detail} |\n824: \n825: ---\n826: \n827: ## Dependencies\n828: \n829: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n830: |---------|---------|---------|\n831: | Helm | ≥3.0 | Chart packaging and deployment |\n832: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | API compatibility |\n833: | Redis | Any | External dependency (session storage) |\n834: \n835: ---\n836: \n837: ## Acceptance Checklist\n838: \n839: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` — Chart metadata with correct apiVersion, name, version\n840: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` — Complete configuration tree for all components\n841: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with correct env/probes\n842: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n843: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n844: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` — Conditional Router RBAC\n845: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — Conditional Volcano Scheduler\n846: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml` — Redis password Secret\n847: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml` — AgentRuntime CRD (existing, verify completeness)\n848: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml` — CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n849: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore` — Ignore patterns for packaging\n850: - [ ] `helm lint` passes without errors\n851: - [ ] `helm template` generates valid YAML\n852: - [ ] `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n853: - [ ] Optional components render correctly when enabled/disabled\n854: - [ ] Values overrides work correctly for multi-environment support\n855: \n856: ---\n857: \n858: ## Open Questions\n859: \n860: 1. Should the chart support external Redis Operator integration?\n861: 2. Should monitoring and logging configurations be integrated into the chart?\n862: 3. Should multi-cluster deployment be supported through values configuration?\n863: 4. Should the chart include default values for development/testing environments?\n\n(End of file - total 863 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** Helm Chart implementation for AgentCube control plane components\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md, deployment/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-030.1: Chart.yaml Metadata\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Chart.yaml with apiVersion v1, name agentcube, version 0.1.0, and appVersion 1.0.0.\n\n#### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879941241,"end":1775879941290}}}}
