{"type":"text","timestamp":1775879963578,"sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab1beef001QTJlKdAQSeA7g6","messageID":"msg_d7ab1b5a5001jNTunAHrgOL2YT","sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the context. AR-030 covers the Helm chart implementation, and AR-031 appears to be about standalone RBAC configuration (ServiceAccount, Role, Binding) that can be applied independently without Helm. Let me write the delta-spec.md for AR-031:","time":{"start":1775879963575,"end":1775879963575}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880064230,"sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab1c3b9001iyJZinrgB4kCkU","messageID":"msg_d7ab1b5a5001jNTunAHrgOL2YT","sessionID":"ses_2854ec89dffen2z48sAPKohq78","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_61d91a71fae848849e39b125","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Standalone RBAC manifests for ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding\n\n**Base Specs:** manifests/delta-spec.md (AR-030), manifests/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-031.1: ServiceAccount Manifests\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ServiceAccount manifests for WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano Scheduler components.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount metadata\n- **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n- **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n  - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n\n#### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/router.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/router.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount metadata\n- **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n- **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: agentcube-router`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n  - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount metadata\n- **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n- **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n  - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: volcano-agent-scheduler`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: scheduler`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.2: ClusterRole Manifests\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ClusterRole manifests defining permissions for WorkloadManager and Volcano Scheduler.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a ClusterRole named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole sandbox permissions\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole extension resources\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole warm pool status\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`, `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole core resources\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"pods\", \"secrets\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole token review\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a ClusterRole named `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole CRD permissions\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole pod permissions\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include comprehensive pod permissions:\n  - `resources: [\"pods\", \"pods/status\", \"pods/binding\", \"pods/disruptionbudgets\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"persistentvolumeclaims\", \"persistentvolumes\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"nodes\", \"namespaces\", \"services\", \"replicationcontrollers\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole scheduling permissions\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"priorityclasses\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n  - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.incubator.k8s.io\", \"scheduling.volcano.sh\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"podgroups\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\", \"update\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole storage permissions\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"storage.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"storageclasses\", \"csinodes\", \"csidrivers\", \"csistoragecapacities\", \"volumeattachments\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole configmap permissions\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"update\"]`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.3: ClusterRoleBinding Manifests\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ClusterRoleBinding manifests binding ClusterRoles to ServiceAccounts.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a ClusterRoleBinding named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding subject\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n- **WHEN** subjects are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding roleRef\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n- **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `kind: ClusterRole`\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a ClusterRoleBinding named `volcano-agent-scheduler-role` SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding subject\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n- **WHEN** subjects are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding roleRef\n- **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n- **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `kind: ClusterRole`\n  - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n  - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.4: Role Manifests (Namespace-Scoped)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped Role manifests for Router component.\n\n#### Scenario: Router Role creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `roles/router.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f roles/router.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a Role named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Router Role secret permissions\n- **GIVEN** the Role is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Router Role configmap permissions\n- **GIVEN** the Role is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Router Role pod permissions\n- **GIVEN** the Role is created\n- **WHEN** rules are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.5: RoleBinding Manifests (Namespace-Scoped)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RoleBinding manifests binding Roles to ServiceAccounts.\n\n#### Scenario: Router RoleBinding creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `rolebindings/router.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f rolebindings/router.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a RoleBinding named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Router RoleBinding subject\n- **GIVEN** the RoleBinding is created\n- **WHEN** subjects are validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - `name: agentcube-router`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n\n#### Scenario: Router RoleBinding roleRef\n- **GIVEN** the RoleBinding is created\n- **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `kind: Role`\n  - `name: agentcube-router`\n  - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.6: Namespace Management\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace manifest and support namespace creation before RBAC application.\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace manifest creation\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `namespace.yaml` is applied\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** a namespace named `agentcube-system` SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace metadata\n- **GIVEN** the namespace is created\n- **WHEN** namespace is validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include labels:\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom namespace support\n- **GIVEN** user wants to use custom namespace\n- **WHEN** manifests are applied with `--namespace` flag\n- **THEN** all RBAC resources SHALL be created in the specified namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace fallback\n- **GIVEN** no namespace is specified\n- **WHEN** manifests are applied\n- **THEN** resources SHALL be created in `agentcube-system` namespace (from manifest) or `default` namespace\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.7: Combined RBAC Manifest\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a combined RBAC manifest that applies all RBAC resources in correct order.\n\n#### Scenario: Combined manifest existence\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `rbac.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f rbac.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** all ServiceAccounts, ClusterRoles, ClusterRoleBindings, Roles, and RoleBindings SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: Correct resource ordering\n- **GIVEN** the combined manifest is applied\n- **WHEN** resources are created\n- **THEN** order SHALL be:\n  1. ServiceAccounts\n  2. ClusterRoles\n  3. ClusterRoleBindings\n  4. Roles\n  5. RoleBindings\n\n#### Scenario: Combined manifest labels\n- **GIVEN** the combined manifest is applied\n- **WHEN** resources are created\n- **THEN** all resources SHALL include common label:\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.8: RBAC Validation and Verification\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide validation scripts and commands to verify RBAC configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: RBAC validation script\n- **GIVEN** the script `validate-rbac.sh` exists\n- **WHEN** `./validate-rbac.sh` is executed\n- **THEN** script SHALL verify all ServiceAccounts exist\n\n#### Scenario: ClusterRole permissions check\n- **GIVEN** the validation script is executed\n- **WHEN** ClusterRoles are checked\n- **THEN** script SHALL verify all required permissions are present\n\n#### Scenario: Binding verification\n- **GIVEN** the validation script is executed\n- **WHEN** bindings are checked\n- **THEN** script SHALL verify all ServiceAccounts are bound to correct roles\n\n#### Scenario: RBAC verification report\n- **GIVEN** the validation script completes\n- **WHEN** report is generated\n- **THEN** output SHALL include:\n  - List of all ServiceAccounts\n  - List of all ClusterRoles with permission counts\n  - List of all bindings with subjects\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.9: Multi-Namespace Support\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL support deploying RBAC for multiple namespaces.\n\n#### Scenario: Multi-namespace ServiceAccount\n- **GIVEN** manifests are applied to multiple namespaces\n- **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/ -n namespace1` and `-n namespace2` are executed\n- **THEN** ServiceAccounts SHALL be created in both namespaces\n\n#### Scenario: ClusterRole reuse across namespaces\n- **GIVEN** ClusterRoles are cluster-scoped\n- **WHEN** multiple namespaces use the same Component\n- **THEN** single ClusterRole SHALL be shared across namespaces\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace-specific RoleBindings\n- **GIVEN** multiple namespaces are configured\n- **WHEN** RoleBindings are created\n- **THEN** each namespace SHALL have its own RoleBinding referencing namespace-specific ServiceAccount\n\n---\n\n### REQ-031.10: RBAC Cleanup\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide cleanup manifests and scripts to remove RBAC resources.\n\n#### Scenario: RBAC cleanup manifest\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `rbac-cleanup.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `kubectl delete -f rbac-cleanup.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** all RBAC resources SHALL be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: Correct cleanup ordering\n- **GIVEN** cleanup is executed\n- **WHEN** resources are deleted\n- **THEN** order SHALL be:\n  1. RoleBindings\n  2. Roles\n  3. ClusterRoleBindings\n  4. ClusterRoles\n  5. ServiceAccounts\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace-preserved cleanup\n- **GIVEN** cleanup is executed with `--preserve-namespace`\n- **WHEN** resources are deleted\n- **THEN** namespace SHALL NOT be deleted, only RBAC resources\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```yaml\n# ServiceAccount structure\nserviceAccount:\n  apiVersion: v1\n  kind: ServiceAccount\n  metadata:\n    name: string\n    namespace: string\n    labels:\n      app.kubernetes.io/name: string\n      app.kubernetes.io/component: string\n\n# ClusterRole structure\nclusterRole:\n  apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  metadata:\n    name: string\n  rules:\n    - apiGroups: [string]\n      resources: [string]\n      verbs: [string]\n\n# ClusterRoleBinding structure\nclusterRoleBinding:\n  apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n  kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n  metadata:\n    name: string\n  roleRef:\n    kind: ClusterRole\n    name: string\n    apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  subjects:\n    - kind: ServiceAccount\n      name: string\n      namespace: string\n\n# Role structure (namespace-scoped)\nrole:\n  apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n  kind: Role\n  metadata:\n    name: string\n    namespace: string\n  rules:\n    - apiGroups: [string]\n      resources: [string]\n      verbs: [string]\n\n# RoleBinding structure (namespace-scoped)\nroleBinding:\n  apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n  kind: RoleBinding\n  metadata:\n    name: string\n    namespace: string\n  roleRef:\n    kind: Role\n    name: string\n    apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  subjects:\n    - kind: ServiceAccount\n      name: string\n      namespace: string\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/rbac/\n├── README.md\n├── namespace.yaml\n├── serviceaccounts/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n│   ├── router.yaml\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n├── clusterroles/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n├── clusterrolebindings/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n├── roles/\n│   └── router.yaml\n├── rolebindings/\n│   └── router.yaml\n├── rbac.yaml              # Combined manifest\n├── rbac-cleanup.yaml      # Cleanup manifest\n└── validate-rbac.sh       # Validation script\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Target namespace for RBAC resources | `agentcube-system` |\n| `KUBECONFIG` | Kubernetes config file | `~/.kube/config` |\n\n---\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Error | Exit Code | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Namespace not found | 1 | `Namespace '{namespace}' does not exist. Run: kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml` |\n| ServiceAccount not found | 1 | `ServiceAccount '{name}' not found in namespace '{namespace}'` |\n| ClusterRole not found | 1 | `ClusterRole '{name}' not found` |\n| Binding failure | 1 | `Failed to bind {role} to {serviceAccount}: {detail}` |\n| Permission denied | 1 | `RBAC: User '{user}' cannot {verb} {resource}` |\n| Invalid manifest syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | RBAC API (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n| kubectl | ≥1.21 | Manifest application and validation |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/namespace.yaml` — Namespace manifest with correct labels\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/router.yaml` — Router ServiceAccount\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRole with all permissions\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole with scheduling permissions\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/roles/router.yaml` — Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/rolebindings/router.yaml` — Router RoleBinding\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac.yaml` — Combined manifest with correct ordering\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac-cleanup.yaml` — Cleanup manifest with reverse ordering\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/validate-rbac.sh` — Validation script\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/README.md` — Usage documentation\n- [ ] `kubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/` succeeds without errors\n- [ ] Validation script reports all resources as healthy\n- [ ] Cleanup removes all RBAC resources correctly\n- [ ] Multi-namespace deployment works correctly\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should RBAC manifests support fine-grained permission customization through overlay files?\n2. Should the validation script integrate with CI/CD pipelines for automated RBAC testing?\n3. Should RBAC manifests include PodSecurityPolicy or PodSecurityStandard bindings?\n4. Should there be separate RBAC profiles (minimal, standard, full) for different security requirements?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880064067,"end":1775880064226}}}}
